<HEAD>Fire Brigade Rouses Sleeper To Home Burning Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SWANSEA, Wales (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John Myfsud was sound asleep in his bed
upstairs when an ultra-polite firefighter tapped him on the shoulder
and said: ``Excuse me sir, your house is burning down.''
   Myfsud, 28, a builder, had slept through an explosion in his
television receiver which started a fire downstairs at his home in
Swansea, south Wales, early Wednesday.
   Neighbour Margery Davies said she saw the smoke and raised the
alarm.
   Myfsud got out safely but his row house was gutted.
