<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BunglingBurglar     11-17 0201</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Bungling Burglar,0204</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Burglar Breaks Ankle, Calls Police To Pick Him Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILLISTON, N.D. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man charged with burglarizing three
grain elevators summoned police to the scene of one of his alleged
crimes when he broke his ankle as he wrestled with a door,
authorities said.
   Harry Dowell, 58, was listed in good condition at Mercy Hospital,
where he was taken after he injured himself at the City Elevator
Inc., authorities said.
   Police arrested Dowell at the elevator after he telephoned
authorities early Wednesday, identified himself as a burglar and
said he had hurt his left leg, Police Capt. Steve Molinari said.
   Dowell told police he had broken into two other elevators,
Molinari said, and he was charged with three counts of felony
burglary.
   Dowell, who was released from the South Dakota State Penitentiary
earlier this month after serving almost seven years for burglary,
fell and hurt his ankle as he was trying to close a sliding door at
City Elevator, Molinari said. He told police he had decided to spend
the night there.
   Dowell crawled to the office area, where he made himself coffee
and enjoyed a few lollipops before the pain prompted him to call
police.
</TEXT>
