<HEAD>With PM-Greenhouse-States</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a state-by-state list of carbon
emissions for 1986 compiled by Renew America, a Washington-based
environmental organization.
   Following each state's name are four figures, each expressed in
millions of metric tons: 1-total emissions from fossil fuel use;
2-emissions from oil; 3-emissions from coal; 4-emissions from
natural gas; The final figure gives the number of tons of carbon
produced per $1 million of gross state product.
