<2ND_LINE>PM-Pakistan-Glance,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pakistan At A Glance</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Pakistan-Election, Bjt</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Here are some facts and figures on Pakistan, where Benazir
Bhutto's populist Pakistan People's Party appeared heading for
victory today after the first free national elections in morre than
a decade:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   THE LAND _ Pakistan covers 310,000 square miles, more than the
state of Texas. Its neighbors are Iran on the west, Afghanistan to
the northwest, the Soviet Union to the north and India on the east.
The four main provinces are Punjab, Sind, Baluchistan and North West
Frontier.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   THE PEOPLE _ Of the 107 million people, two-thirds are of the
Punjabi ethnic group and 97 percent are Moslem. Urdu is the official
language but English is widely used.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   THE GOVERNMENT _ Pakistan has a parliamentary system. The
president is chief of state and the prime minister, chosen from the
National Assembly, is chief of government.
</TEXT>
