<HEAD>Duck Hunter Charged With Shooting Airplane</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EARLEVILLE, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A duck hunter has been charged with
shooting a low-flying research airplane along the Chesapeake Bay's
Eastern Shore.
   Steven James Zang, 31, was arraigned Tuesday on charges of
assault and malicious destruction of property.
   He was accused of firing on the four-seat private aircraft from a
duck blind Oct. 8, said Maryland Department of Natural Resources
