<2ND_LINE>PM-Family Attacked,0251</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Shot After Family Bound and Gagged During Robbery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONTVILLE, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A masked gunman in black terrorized a coin
dealer and his family and then shot and killed the man as he tried
to flee, authorities said.
   The gunman handcuffed and blindfolded Roy A. Edwards, his wife,
Irene, and two daughters Tuesday night, and assaulted all four, said
Lt. Jack Dempsey of the Morris County prosecutor's office. Dempsey
gave no other details on the assaults.
   One daughter was hospitalized.
   Officials said they believe the robber singled out the home,
where Edwards ran a part-time coin dealership, because he asked for
coins. Authorities said they have no suspects but believe the gunman
knew the family's daily routine.
   Edwards, 43, was shot in the neck and died instantly after he
bolted from the upstairs bedroom, where the family had been tied up,
and ran downstairs and into the back yard, Dempsey said. Mrs.
Edwards then began screaming for help.
   ``I heard a commotion,'' said Marv Vandenberg, who was walking
his dogs. ``I got down on the corner and heard heard `Help me!' I
proceeded up (the street). I could hear her scream again. She said,
`Somebody's attacking my husband!'''
   The robber got away with $700 from Mrs. Edwards' purse, Dempsey
said.
   The couple's 9-year-old daughter, Ilene, was listed in stable
condition today at Morristown Memorial Hospital. Mrs. Edwards and
the other daughter, Deidra, 7, were treated at the hospital and
released.
</TEXT>
