   ``I don't know,'' he said. ``Maybe so, but I'm not sure.
   For his part, Sununu refused to confirm at a new conference in
Concord on Wednesday that Bush has tapped him for White House chief
of staff.
   ``A request isn't a formal request until the tall thin guy
sings,'' Sununu said. ``And the tall thin guy hasn't sung publicly,
and therefore I'm not going to comment.''
