on the second-story roof of a three-story rowhouse, threatening to
kill himself.
   The police car was stolen Nov. 8 while a trooper visited
relatives. In the trunk were a grenade launcher, tear gas grenades,
a submachine gun, a revolver, two shotguns, ammunition and
rappelling hooks and other equipment used to scale buildings.
   City police found the car about two hours after it was reported
missing. Its trunk had been forced open and the weapons were missing.
