<HEAD>Student In Custody After University Dorm Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A prank produced a fire that gutted a
dormitory room and forced the evacuation of about 380 students today
at Southeast Missouri State University, and a student was arrested,
police said.
   The dormitory was evacuated at 12:45 a.m., police Sgt. Carl
Kinnison said. Students spent the night at the university sports and
entertainment arena.
   Kinnison said students were lighting tissue paper and sliding it
under doors to surprise dorm mates. However, one room was unoccupied
and the door was locked, and the prank sparked a fire that fed on
posters and other items.
   The student arrested will probably be charged with reckless
burning, a misdemeanor, and a second student may also be charged,
Kinnison said.
