<HEAD>Soldier Guilty of Murdering Good Samaritan in Rape Drama</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A soldier was found guilty Thursday of
killing a farmer who tried to stop him from raping a 13-year-old
girl.
   Timothy Mhlanga was sentenced to death after being found guilty
of murder by Judge Ahmed Ebrahim and two civilian assessors in the
High Court. He also was sentenced to 10 years in prison for the rape
conviction.
   According to testimony, Mhlanga, one of 30 soldiers guarding a
bridge on the Mazoe River in northeastern Zimbabwe on Aug. 13, 1987,
was raping the girl when a man and his son walking nearby heard her
cries for help.
   Mhlanga opened fire at the two, killing Chakanetsa Zhogi. The son
escaped.
   Mhlanga, who pleaded innocent, testified he suspected the Zhogi
and his son were dissidents. He also said he had fought as a
guerrilla for President Robert Mugabe in the seven-year war that led
to Zimbabwe's independence from Britain in 1980.
