<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Belgium-Crashes     11-17 0141</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Belgium-Crashes,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two F-16 Jets Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAULILLE, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Belgian air force F-16 jet fighters
crashed Thursday in separate incidents, and their pilots escaped
injury, the Defense Ministry said.
   The pilots ejected and parachuted to safety.
   The first plane had taken off from the nearby air force base of
Kleine Brogel and was on a training flight when it hit birds and
crashed in Kaulille, a ministry official said.
   Military investigators had gone to the scene near the Dutch
border, about 60 miles northeast of Brussels, the capital, said the
official, who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   The second plane crashed in Willbringen, 19 miles east of
Brussels. No reason was given for the crash.
   The crashes brought to 19 the number of F-16s lost by the Belgian
air force since it started using the planes in 1979.
</TEXT>
