<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Elton John,0230</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pop Star, Wife Announce Divorce Plans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pop star Elton John and his wife, Renate, announced
Thursday they have separated and plan to divorce because after four
years of marriage ``we are growing apart.''
   They said in a statement they were saddened, but were ``parting
on the most amicable terms and genuinely intend to remain best
friends.''
   The divorce, ``by mutual consent,'' will come into effect
automatically in two years, they said. They have no children.
   ``Both of us have been, and will be, so busy with our own work
commitments that we are seeing too little of each other _ and for
this reason it seems unavoidable that we are growing apart,'' they
said.
   The statement quoted John's 34-year-old wife as saying: ``We are
both confident that all personal matters will be resolved without
any animosity. I am obviously saddened to see our marriage end. I
wish Elton all the happiness in the world, and I know that he wishes
me the same.'''
   It added that no information about the financial terms of the
settlement would be released and no further statements would be
issued.
   John, 41, married Ms. Blauel, a German-born recording engineer,
in a show-business wedding in 1984 in Sydney, Australia, where he
was on a concert tour. He has sold more than 80 million records.
</TEXT>
