<HEAD>Police Seize $10 Million in of Cocaine, Arrest Four Smugglers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police on Thursday said they
arrested three Dominicans and a Puerto Rican for trying to smuggle
$10 million worth of cocaine from the Dominican Republic.
   Members of a special anti-narcotics squad, the Rapid Action
Force, seized a 36-foot luxury yacht containing 138 pounds of
cocaine Wednesday night two miles off the western coast of Puerto
Rico, said police spokesman Tony Santiago.
