   Santiago estimated the cocaine was worth $10 million. He said the
yacht, which he valued at $125,000, was registered in the United
States but flew a Dominican Republic flag.
   Javier Vazquez, a customs agent in the western town of Mayaguez,
said police boarded the yacht at 10 p.m.
   The four suspects will be arraigned in San Juan Thursday.
