<HEAD>World Sugar Production Expected To Hit Record Level</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   World sugar production in 1988-89 is forecast
at a record of 106.9 million metric tons, up 3 percent from 103.6
million tons last year, the Agriculture Department said Thursday.
   The new forecast was down slightly from 107.1 million tons
indicated by the department in September. The tonnages are expressed
in raw sugar value.
   World production of sugar from cane was forecast at 67.8 million
tons, up 4 percent from last year, and sugar from beets at 39.1
million tons, up 2 percent.
