<HEAD>Hewlett-Packard Revenue Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALO ALTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hewlett-Packard Co. reported Thursday
its fourth-quarter earnings rose 11 percent while the computer
manufacturer's revenue increased 19 percent.
   Hewlett-Packard said its earnings totaled $243 million, or $1.03
a share during the quarter ended Oct. 31, up from $218 million, or
85 cents a share, in the fourth quarter of 1987.
   Revenue rose to $2.71 billion from $2.28 billion in the 1987
quarter.
   Hewlett-Packard president John Young said the company's business
was strong ``on a broad mix of products.''
   For its full fiscal year, Hewlett-Packard said its earnings rose
27 percent to $816 million, or $3.36 a share, from $644 million, or
$2.50 a share, in fiscal 1987.
   Revenue rose to $9.83 billion from 1987's $8.09 billion.
   The company's orders exceeded $10 billion for the first time in
its history and were up 20 percent from a year ago.
   ``Order growth was robust across the globe, but particularly in
the Asia-Pacific region and Europe,'' Young said. ``In Japan, orders
rose approximately 40 percent over fiscal 1987.''
</TEXT>
