<HEAD>Production Falls This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
254,504 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
255,060, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 233,134 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 163,476 cars this week,
compared with 165,997 a week ago and 150,582 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 91,028,
compared with last week's 89,063 and last year's 82,552.
   Canadian automakers were to build 17,883 cars this week, up from
16,207 a week ago but down from last year's 19,613.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,823, compared
with 20,150 a week ago and 17,678 in the same week last year.
