<DOCNO> AP881117-0278 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-11-17-88 1339EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-MasterCard-CEO     11-17 0189</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-MasterCard-CEO,0202</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>First Interstate Exec To Head MasterCard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   MasterCard International on Thursday announced
the appointment of Los Angeles banker Alex W. ``Pete'' Hart as
president and chief executive officer of the giant credit-card
company.
   Hart, a former executive vice president at First Interstate
Bancorp and a MasterCard board member, replaces eight-year veteran
Russell E. Hogg, whose resignation takes effect Friday.
   MasterCard said Hart was elected by the board of the bankcard
association.
   Hart, 48, has an extensive bankground in the credit card business
and with MasterCard.
   He has been a MasterCard director since 1983 and a member of the
executive committee. He also was vice chairman of the board and
would have been chairman in 1989, the company said.
   At First Interstate, Hart ran the consumer banking operation in
Los Angeles. He served, among other things, as chairman of First
Interstate System Inc., the bank franchising subsidiary and First
Interstate Bancard Co. He also is vice chairman at Cirrus, an
international network of automated teller machines.
   MasterCard operates one of the world's largest credit-card
businesses in the world, with more than 150 million cardholders.
</TEXT>
