<HEAD>London Shares Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices rose strongly Thursday on the London
Stock Exchange, boosted by takeover speculation.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 16.3
points, or 0.9 percent, to 1,823.6. The Financial Times 30-share
index was up 10.4 points at 1,487.5 at the close.
   Volume was a moderate 493.6 million shares, compared with the
550.7 shares traded Wednesday.
   Sentiment continued to be bolstered by Wednesday's news that
Britain's General Electric Co. and West Germany's Siemens AG were
offering $3.1 billion for Britain's Plessey Co. PLC, an electronics
company.
   The market was ``rife with (takeover) stories,'' one market maker
said.
   The Financial Times 500-share index rose 8.67 points to close at
1,038.00.
</TEXT>
